===The great floods of 1936 and 1938 and their effects===

[[File:Springfield Massachusetts1938 flood.jpg|thumb|200px|right|Springfield during the 1938 flood]]
 
In 1936, at the height of America's [[Great Depression]], the City of Springfield suffered one of its most devastating natural disasters prior to the tornadoes of 2011. The Connecticut River flooded, reaching record heights, inundating the South End and the North End neighborhoods, where some of Springfield's finest mansions stood. Damages were estimated at [[United States dollar|$]]200,000,000 in 1936 dollars.
